ALGORITHM ANALYZER

1. Introduction

Search algorithms are fundamental to artificial intelligence and machine learning. They are used to explore state spaces and find optimal paths or solutions. Different algorithms follow different strategies leading to variations in performance, cost and efficiency.
This project, "Algorithm Analyzer", is designed to implement and compare multiple search algorithms ( namely BFS, DFS, Hill climbing, A*, Best First Search ) on a user-defined graph. The system evaluates each algorithm and identifies the most efficient one based on path cost.

2. Objectives
The main objectives of this project are:

* To implement various search algorithms in Python
* To analyze and compare their performance
* To determine the most optimal path from start to goal node
* To understand the role of heuristics in informed search algorithms
* To build a system that automates algorithm comparison

3. Scope of the Project
This project focuses on:

* Graph-based problem solving
* Comparison of uninformed and informed search algorithms
* Cost-based path optimization

4. Algorithms Used

4.1 Breadth First Search (BFS)

* Explores nodes level by level ( breadth wise)
* Guarantees shortest path in terms of steps
* Does not consider heuristic cost

4.2 Depth First Search (DFS)

* Explores deeply into one branch before backtracking ( depth wise)
* Does not guarantee optimal solution

4.3 A* Algorithm

* Uses function:
  f(n) = g(n) + h(n)
* Combines actual cost and heuristic
* Guarantees optimal solution if heuristic is accurate

4.4 Best First Search

* Uses heuristic function only
f(n)=h(n)
* Selects node closest to goal
* Faster but not always optimal

4.5 Hill Climbing

* Greedy approach
* Moves to best neighboring node
* May get stuck in local maxima, ridge problem and plateau problem.

5. System Design

5.1 Input

* Graph (nodes and weighted edges)
* Heuristic values
* Start node
* Goal node

5.2 Processing

* Each algorithm runs independently
* Path and cost are calculated
* Results are compared

5.3 Output

* Path found by each algorithm
* Total cost of each algorithm
* Best algorithm based on minimum cost

6. Implementation Details

* Programming Language: Python
* Data Structures Used:

  * Graph (Dictionary)
  * Queue (BFS)
  * Stack (DFS)
  * Priority Queue (A*, Best First)

